thread.title: Rangers' Profar homers in Arizona Fall League debut
thread.title_full: Rangers' Profar homers in Arizona Fall League debut | Dallas Morning News

author: Gerry Fraley
title: Rangers' Profar homers in Arizona Fall League debut
text:
Jurickson Profar, the Rangers' oft-injured middle infielder, had two extra-base hits in his Arizona Fall League debut on Thursday.
In his first at-bat with Surprise, Profar doubled against right-hander Aaron Wilkerson, a former Grand Prairie Air Hog now in the Boston organization. In the ninth, he hit a game-tying homer against right-hander Montreal Robertson, of the Detroit organization.
Profar will be limited to designated-hitter appearances in the AFL, a gathering of top prospects. Hitters tend do have the upper hand in the league.
Profar has not played the field since a spring-training game on March 22, 2014, because of a damaged muscle in the right shoulder. The Rangers have Profar on a restricted throwing program. He will continue to rehabilitate the shoulder after the AFL ends on Nov. 19 but will not move on to a winter league.
Outfielder Lewis Brinson, ranked among the top prospects in the Rangers' player-development system, had two hits and drove in one run. Brinson has a .385 on-base percentage through six games.
